<TEXT>
us officials formally inaugurated a 
68mile stretch of road built in a sixmonth project involving 
more than 9000 us soldiers and national guardsmen 
the american troops who started the project dec 28 built a 
road linking jocon a village in rural yoro province and puente 
grande about 200 honduran troops also took part in the project 
honduran and american army and national guard units have held a 
series of joint operations with the us forces being rotated in 
and out of the country for brief periods of duty 
the final report at a ceremony monday marking the conclusion of 
the roadbuilding project said the us troops also assisted 11500 
honduran civilians and 8000 animals in health and veterinary 
programs 
gen frederick woener chief of the us southern command based 
in panama attended the ceremony 
us embassy sources who spoke on condition of anonymity said 
another roadbuilding exercise is planned in the summer of 1989 to 
build 55 miles of road between jocon and the village of san 
lorenzo 
at least 60 joint military exercises involving us and honduran 
forces have been held in the past six years 
the program began after the reagan administration claimed 
nicaraguas leftwing sandinista regime threatened other central 
american countries 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

