<DOCNO> AP880621-0031 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
stifling temperatures are adding to the 
droughtinduced misery in parts of america but even the 104degree 
record set in lincoln neb is 30 degrees short of the national 
alltime high 
record highs recorded in the midwest and plains this week 
include sundays 104 degrees at lincoln breaking a record of 103 
for the date set in 1974 95 degrees in alpena mich topping the 
92degree mark of 1964 and 103 in sioux city iowa beating the 
99degree record set in 1933 and 1953 
the highest official reading in the united states was set july 
10 1913 in death valley calif when the thermometer reached 134 
degrees fahrenheit 
death valley has the perfect conditions for setting heat 
records low elevation in an already warm area clear skies and 
subsiding air on the lee side of mountains geographer david h 
hickcox says in weatherwise magazine 
even so it seldom reaches the sweltering heights of the 130s 
rarely exceeding 127 degrees hickcox reports but it is steadily 
hot with the daily high falling below 105 only once during june of 
1987 for example 
while death valley gets the attention however high temperature 
records of more than 100 degrees have been set in every state at 
one time or another 
even seemingly frigid alaska has managed the century mark 
recording 100 degrees at fort yukon on june 27 1915 
that ties hawaii where the 100degree record was set at pahala 
on april 27 1931 
alaska and hawaii with their records of 100 degrees tie for 
the lowest such record 
