some crops but damaged others such as cherries 
washington state grange master ray hill is one who stands to 
both benefit and lose because of the drought 
hill a wheat grower and cattle rancher said he will make more 
money this year on wheat which is selling at nearly 1 a bushel 
more than last year due to the anticipated shortfall from the 
drought 
