drought and our wheat prices are based on those 
last year farmers received about 260 per bushel they are now 
looking at 335 to 350 a bushel mick said it is possible price 
rises will continue through the august harvest of washingtons and 
oregons predominantly soft white variety of wheat used for 
noodles and pasta 
midwest farmers grow a hard red variety thats used primarily in 
bread 
