<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap lt gen henri namphy publicly 
running haiti again after four months of civilian government is a 
55yearold career soldier associates describe as forceful 
dedicated and patriotic 
namphy returned to power early monday in a coup that deposed the 
civilian president to whom he transferred power in february he had 
run the government since dictator jeanclaude duvalier fled the 
ocuntry feb 7 1986 
the general who had commanded duvaliers armed forces appeared 
on television a few hours after duvalier left in a us air force 
plane to announce formation of a provisional council that would 
govern and arrange a fair good and firm transition to 
democracy 
he was president of the council which eventually was reduced to 
a threeman junta and turned over power feb 7 to president leslie 
manigat who was elected the previous month with the armys help 
namphy is a solidly built man of medium height with steelgray 
eyes and closely cropped graying hair 
during his two years in the national palace namphy told 
associates he preferred life at home or in the barracks and spent 
weekends at his house with friends relaxing in his pool he and 
his wife gabrielle have an 11yearold daughter melissa 
born into a lowermiddle class family in northern haiti namphy 
attended a roman catholic elementary school in portauprince and 
the haitian military academy he speaks french creole and spanish 
at age 22 namphy was commissioned a lieutenant by francois 
papa doc duvalier jeanclaudes father 
in 1982 as a colonel he led the campaign against a small band 
of rebels who landed in northern haiti he was promoted to 
lieutenant general and soon after to chief of staff 
if i had to choose being president of this country is not 
what i would have chosen namphy said in an interview with the 
associated press in october 1986 i have only one thing to say to 
whoever is going to become president dont be late for the 
inauguration because im not going to wait around 
at my age i have never voted i dont know what voting is 
about i have to have my own civic education and if i need that 
you have to believe the people need that too 
he has shown little trust in democratic processes and appears to 
prefer ruling by decree 
when it was obvious that strongly antiduvalier candidates had 
the best chance of winning elections nov 29 1987 namphy tried to 
seize control from the independent electoral council soldiers 
killed at least 30 people when haitians held demonstrations that 
combined with diplomatic pressure forced namphy to back down 
he looked the other way as produvalier elements prohibited by 
the new constitution from running for office mounted a terror 
campaign against the election 
the electoral councils headquarters was burned and its members 
went into hiding on election day soldiers and thugs killed at 
least 34 voters and the election was called off three hours after 
it began 
namphy dissolved the electoral council and appointed a new 
electoral body to hold the jan 17 elections 
