courageous and farsighted changes which are commonly believed 
necessary in the economic social and political spheres the 
bishops said 
referring to the authorities announced plans to make it easier 
to form private associations the bishops said this may 
contribute to the rise of creative activity in the society 
but they said the changes must create freedom of associating 
accessible for all regardless of political viewpoint and 
eliminate administrative and political interference in associations 
even farreaching changes in this field will not replace the 
need of trade union pluralism which according to the social 
teaching of the church belongs to the basic rights of working 
people the statement adds 
trade union pluralism is one of the basic demands of solidarity 
which has remained active though it was banned after a december 
1981 military crackdown 
about 50 solidarity local organizations have sought registration 
in the courts over the past year but all have been denied it on 
the grounds officially recognized unions already exist at the 
plants 
government spokesman jerzy urban said poor economic conditions 
discouraged some people from attending sundays voting but argued 
that the elections were a breakthrough because some candidates 
actively campaigned for the first time and some races were 
contested between people of different parties 
