captured many of their likenesses 
the artist known for his caricatures of celebrities as diverse 
as humphrey bogart superman and albert einstein estimates 
conservatively that he has sketched more than 3000 drawings 
hirschfeld draws the caricatures in the studio of his east side 
town house while sitting in an old barber chair in front of a 
heavily scarred wooden drawing table 
in an interview with the new york times where many of the 
artists caricatures are published hirschfeld said his career 
began in the 1920s when a friend who happened to be a press agent 
took a look at a caricature he had sketched on a program during a 
theater performance 
that sketch was sold to the herald tribune which wanted another 
one the following week about a year later the times started 
requesting sketches and hirschfeld kept them coming over the years 
hirschfeld said drawing feeds his insatiable appetite for pure 
line for distillation for bringing things down to the simplest 
form 
what i do across all the years of staring at a blank piece of 
paper is create a new problem every time and then solve it to my 
own satisfaction he said 
hirschfelds drawings all contain a game for the viewer the 
name of his daughter nina appears in all the sketches and the 
number of times the name appears is revealed next to the artists 
name 
nina was born on oct 20 1945 and on that day i put in a 
drawing in a circus poster in the background a little baby 
reading a book called nina the wonder child he said and 
since then it has become a national insanity 
the times article today played on the game with a small 6 
next to the byline indicating there were six ninas in the text 
including one hidden in the first four paragraphs 
