with a foreign bank in milan activity has essentially halted to 
see whether theres going to be any reaction to the movements in 
interest rates 
he added that the rate hike already had been discounted by the 
market 
the market also was in a waitandsee mood over the toronto 
economic summit of the seven major industrialized countries 
although the summit which ends today wasnt expected to 
produce any major developments for the currency markets traders 
were on their guard for any statements that could affect the dollar 
in tokyo where the business day ends before europes begins 
the dollar rose 024 yen to a closing 12633 later in london it 
was quoted at 12645 yen 
