the west 
the italian communists have been excluded from government since 
1947 but they were at the threshold of power in the mid1970s when 
led by enrico berlinguer who declared the partys independence 
from moscow in 1976 the party captured 344 percent of the vote 
natta who took over after berlinguers death in 1984 pledged 
to follow his policies but lacked his political charisma 
the party entered a period of drift and in 1987 suffered its 
worst election defeat in 20 years slipping to 266 percent of the 
vote for the chamber of deputies in parliament last month the 
communists won only 219 percent of the vote in local elections 
occhetto on monday noted that the partys traditional base of 
support had shrunk and pledged to work for a new communist 
party 
the communist leader heavyset with a graying walrus mustache 
