months it has seized some 57 million units of illegal fireworks in 
a cooperative program with the us customs service at 15 ports of 
entry 
problems found in the products included overloaded fireworks 
defective fuses unstable bases casings which blow out on the side 
and improper warning labels 
the commission said approximately 9000 injuries involving 
fireworks were treated at hospital emergency rooms last year down 
from 12600 in 1986 
to avoid becoming one of those statistics scanlon offered a 
series of safety tips 
always read and follow label instructions 
ignite fireworks outdoors only 
make sure an an adult is present whenever fireworks are used 
have a bucket of water at hand in the event of a fire and for 
dousing apparent duds 
never try to relight a firework that does not go off 
never carry fireworks in a pocket and dont throw them 
light only one at a time 
do not set off fireworks in a metal or glass container 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

