<TEXT>
a deadly thunderstorm that caused the 
1985 crash of a delta air lines jumbo jet was visible to air 
traffic controllers but not to the aircrafts flight crew a delta 
pilot testified 
capt william melvin chairman of a safety committee for the 
airline pilots association also said the crew of flight 191 may 
have been set up by wind shear training because flight 
simulators did not include conditions comparable to the storm that 
caused the crash 
he the pilot could see the clouds he could see rain 
melvin testified monday but he couldnt see the cloud 
development because he was too close 
melvin a dallasbased pilot and wind shear expert who was part 
of the initial crash investigation was deltas final witness in a 
nonjury trial being heard by us district judge david o belew jr 
the l1011 widebody crashed aug 2 1985 killing 137 people and 
injuring 25 others while trying to land at dallasfort worth 
international airport 
delta claims government meteorologists and air traffic 
controllers failed to inform the crew of the worsening weather and 
wants the government to pay all or part of the claims facing the 
atlantabased airline delta and its insurance companies already 
have paid more than 90 million in death injury and damage claims 
and the final total is expected to exceed 100 million 
echoing testimony earlier in the trial by william haggard a 
meteorologist melvin said he believed a smaller milder rain cell 
masked the highaltitude development of the severe storm from the 
flight crew 
but observers south of the storm where air traffic controllers 
were located could clearly see the development melvin said 
national transportation safety board investigators determined 
that the crash resulted from a microburst a severe downburst from 
a thunderstorm their report said the microburst contained several 
wind shears or strong abrupt shifts in wind direction 
melvin said the crash was the first to document the presence of 
more than one wind shear in a single storm computerized wind shear 
models used in cockpit simulator training before the flight 191 
crash contained only one wind shear he testified 
the way pilots were trained is once you get through these 
things there wasnt any more said melvin that could have set 
up the pilots of delta 191 
lawyers for the government which contends the flight crew 
should have been able to avoid the crash are expected to begin 
presenting their case next week the trial which has been 
continuing for over three months is expected to continue for 
several more months 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

