the summit including a promotion of international attempts to 
reduce acid rain and protect water resources particularly the 
north sea 
he said he would continue to pursue his goal of seeking to tie 
protection of tropical rain forests to helping debtridden 
countries adding that doubtless the world bank has an important 
role to play 
the bank has been criticized for funding projects that destroy 
the forests and the valuable resources they provide the banks 
projects sometimes have included conversions of the forests into 
farms that soon fail and turn to desert 
improvement of the plight of poor countries is also closely tied 
to the fight against trade protection he said 
without open markets the developing countries have no chance 
to improve their situation for the long term he said 
