<TEXT>
us surgeon general c everett koop 
honored a florida high school parentteacher group tuesday at the 
national pta convention for staging the most effective aids 
education program 
in a speech to the annual convention koop also reiterated his 
belief that parents and educators must teach youngsters about all 
sexual practices that carry a risk of transmitting aids 
i am deeply saddened that we must explain human sexuality 
so that they do not contract the fatal disease but we must koop 
said it is a lifesaving message and we are dutybound to 
deliver it 
koop presented the award to the gainsville high school 
parentteacher association for a project involving more than 100 
faculty and school staff members the 1650member student body 
parents and community members 
the parentteacher group working with local health 
professionals and school personnel conducted a survey to learn 
what students knew about the disease and then arranged inservice 
training for the school staff and coordinated a program for the 
students 
the gainesville educators reported finding that students 
significantly improved their knowledge about how to protect 
themselves against acquired immune deficiency syndrome 
koop noted that of the 65000 reported aids cases in the united 
states since 1981 most involved sexually active male homosexuals 
or intravenous drug abusers who share needles 
but the surgeon general emphasized that the disease will spread 
into a broader population unless parents and educators encourage 
young people to abstain from sex while in school and practice 
monogamy as adults 
if abstinence or monogamy isnt practiced koop said young 
adults must be made aware of the protection afforded by latex 
condoms 
koop implicitly endorsed utahs twotiered aids education 
program 
the program offers one set of lessons for the general school 
population beginning with the third grade and separate more 
detailed lessons for children whose parents request it the program 
is designed to give detailed information without offending a small 
but vocal minority that opposes any sex education 
ive always said you cannot exceed community standards when 
designing an aids curriculum he said otherwise it will never 
fly 
koop said the governments recent educational effort an 
eightpage pamphlet mailed to 107 million american households 
apparently got a favorable reception with the exception of a 
