reporters 
webb ball and aldridge did not know how the fbi had broadened 
the navy investigation however and carlucci did not learn of the 
probe until the day before search warrants were served last week 
howard said 
meanwhile the spokesman said carlucci has issued a directive 
specifying that any pentagon employee who became the subject of 
the investigation must be given substitute duties that will not 
involve them in ongoing procurements or provide them access to 
information related to ongoing procurements 
carlucci took the action so that pentagon purchasing is free 
from question howard said 
