monsanto co on tuesday announced a product for 
keeping produce fresh that it said is an effective alternative to 
sulfite 
the product snow fresh extends the shelf life of most fresh 
processed produce and fruit to at least five days by delaying the 
onset of browning from the effects of air and enzymes monsanto 
said 
monsanto said the product was a blend of four ingredients each 
of which is on the governments list of products generally 
recognized as safe the ingredients are not processed or modified 
in any way monsanto said 
sulfite has been subject to regulatory restrictions because of 
health concerns 
snow fresh comes as a white powder in 50pound pails and is 
mixed with water to form a solution for dipping food into 
the product was introduced by the monsanto chemical co unit of 
st louisbased monsanto in new orleans at the annual meeting of 
the institute of food technologists 
